  "text": "Adult GlyRs are composed of channel-forming α 1-4 and β subunits involved in receptor anchoring [CITATION_1] to form hetero-oligomeric complexes (3α:2β; [CITATION_2] . Only α subunits form functional homomeric channels that contain binding sites for agonists and competitive antagonists (Grenningloh et al., 1990; [CITATION_3] Handford et al., 1996) . Various GlyR α 1-4 subunit isoforms are expressed in distinct regional patterns in the CNS and are developmentally regulated [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] .",
